rComments: The best Professor I've ever had. Incredibly bright, kind and fair. A well designed class with wonderful material and a fantastic teacher who can always further the discussion into something new. Incredibly teacher!

High-school level. Doesn't really do Political Science, but rather a descriptive survey of facts. Nothing you couldn't read in a single book in a couple of hours. Waste of time and not worthy of university education.

She was very clear.  All you need to do is attend lectures and pay attention - she basically spells everything out.  Last lecture is pre-exam overview and she pretty much lists off everything that will be on the exam.
I found Patricia to be a good lecturer. she uses personal experience to illustrate various themes in such a way that they really make sense. a nice lady.

She is very passionate and a kind person, but she digresses into often boring anecdotes from her past work experiences and is very unclear. She is, however, very easy. I recommend focusing on gender issues for the exam as 70% of the final concerned gender
